cs.IT, cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PE 

This paper involves optimization of a wireless communication system for a UAV powered by laser energy harvesting. It involves trajectory optimization and power allocation, which are common topics in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves communication with a ground station, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The energy harvesting constraint and optimization problem formulation are related to control systems (cs.SY) and power engineering (cs.PE).
